info.name: Agent Bank API v2.0
info.description:
# Introduction API for Agent Bank information in PBD.
Exposes endpoints to list, create, update, read and delete a bank in PBD. The endpoints are access restricted and client must have the neccessary privileges to invoke them. # API summary with common use cases ## 1. _List agent banks_ Clients can search a specific agent bank or banks in PBD based on various query parameters. Response will contain all the matching banks with their basic information along with response size `totalSize` and `nextPageToken`. **User Inputs:** (mandatory are marked with asterix) * `page-size`: size of the response list * `page-token`: page number of the list of agent banks * `sortingElement`: sorting element for list of agent banks * `agentBankCriteria`: Different criteria parameters for agent banks ## 2. _Create agent bank_ Clients can create a new agent bank in PBD.
Endpoint responds back with the newly created agent bank upon successful creation. **User Inputs:** Agent Bank details in request body. * `bankParamAgentId` * `agentBic` * `agentSystem` * `agentSubSystem` * `changeStatus` * `endDate` * `startDate` ``` ## 3. _Update agent bank_ Clients can update an existing agent bank. Complete agent bank record is expected along the with the changed fields. If not provided it may result in failure.
Response contains the updated agent bank record. **User Inputs:** Agent Bank details as part of request body. Mandatory fields of the same are mentioned below. *`pk` *`version` * `bankParamAgentId` * `agentBic` * `agentSystem` * `agentSubSystem` * `changeStatus` * `endDate` * `startDate` ``` ## 4. _Read information for agent bank_ Information for a specific agent bank can be accessed via this endpoint. Response contains the complete data just for the requested agent bank along with the ETag value in the response header.
**User Inputs:** (mandatory are marked with asterix) * `agentBankId*`: Describes the agentBankId of the agent Bank as query parameter. --- ## 5. _Close/Delete agent bank_ This operation is used to close/delete agent bank by agentBankId.
This endpoint can close/delete a agent bank. Successful response will give complete information of agent bank.
**User Inputs:** (mandatory are marked with asterix) * `pk*`: Describes the pk of the agent bank record as query parameter. *`version*`: Describes the version of the agent bank record as query parameter. --- # Error response information ``` { "system": "PBD", "code": "3700", "message": "Input error.", "params": null, "applicationSpecific": { "severity": "INPUT_ERROR", "logref": "b85946f2-3044-11e9-b210-d663bd873d93", "message": "Input error.", "validationErrors": [ { errorCode: 3700 errorMessage: page-size maximum value should not exceed 500. } ], "cause": "string" "strackTrace": "string" } } ```
Field Description
system The system short name. Always PBD.
code Error code, identifies uniquely an error type.
message Error message in English describing the error/information situation
params Optional dynamic parameters - can be used to construct an error message in the client.
severity Describes the system level severity of the exception.
logref A log reference associated with the failed request that can be used by support personnel to filter server logs for diagnostic purpose. The caller of the api should save this log reference with its own incident data so it can be part of an incident report.
message Contains addition information about the response in case of an exception.
validationErrors Optional, array of additional details for validation exceptions with errorCode and errorMessage objects.
cause This is development mode property and won't be visible on live. Contains root cause for the exception.
stackTrace This is development mode property and won't be visible on live. Contains the stack trace of the exception.
